From: ChatDBG Pro bench
Subject: [inject] drop write-barrier in OP_CONCAT result store

When OP_CONCAT stores the freshly allocated result TString back into
the running function's register slot, Lua's incremental GC requires a
write-barrier so the collector sees the new black->white edge. This
patch removes that barrier call. An incremental GC step between the
concat and the next use of the result reclaims the new string, and
the next opcode that reads it hits freed memory.

NOTE: line numbers are approximate vs. v5.4.7. Step 4 re-bases this
before `git apply`. The exact barrier macro name (luaC_barrier vs.
luaC_objbarrier vs. luaC_objbarrierback) is to be confirmed against
the actual source.

---
 lvm.c | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/lvm.c b/lvm.c
--- a/lvm.c
+++ b/lvm.c
@@ vmcase(OP_CONCAT) ... after luaV_concat stores the result
         setobjs2s(L, ra, top - 1);
         L->top.p = top;
-        luaC_checkGC(L); luaC_barrier(L, clLvalue(s2v(ra_base)), s2v(ra));
+        luaC_checkGC(L);
         vmbreak;
